In [[differential geometry]], the '''Atiyah–Hitchin–Singer theorem''', introduced by {{harvs|txt|last1=Atiyah|first1=Michael|author1-link=Michael Atiyah|last2=Hitchin|first2=Nigel|author2-link=Nigel Hitchin|last3=Singer|first3=Isadore|author3-link=Isadore Singer|year1=1977|year2=1978}},  states that the space of [[SU(2)]] anti self dual [[Yang–Mills field]]s on a [[4-sphere]] with [[Atiyah–Singer index theorem|index]] ''k''&nbsp;>&nbsp;0 has dimension 8''k''&nbsp;–&nbsp;3.

