A '''dodecahedral number''' is a [[figurate number]] that represents a [[dodecahedron]]. The ''n''th dodecahedral number is given by the formula

<math>{n(3n-1)(3n-2) \over 2}</math>

The first such numbers are 0, 1, 20, 84, 220, 455, 816, 1330, 2024, 2925, 4060, 5456, 7140, 9139, 11480, … {{OEIS|id=A006566}}.

